    "# 6D Behavioural Vector PDM Generation\n",
    "\n",
    "> [1] B. G. Cangan, L. Heintzman, A. Hashimoto, N. Abaid, and R. K. Williams, ‘Anticipatory Human-Robot Path Planning for Search and Rescue’, arXiv:2009.03976 [cs], Sep. 2020, Accessed: Nov. 24, 2021. [Online]. Available: http://arxiv.org/abs/2009.03976\n",
    "\n",
    "> [2] L. Heintzman, A. Hashimoto, N. Abaid, and R. K. Williams, ‘Anticipatory Planning and Dynamic Lost Person Models for Human-Robot Search and Rescue’, in 2021 IEEE International Conference on Robotics and Automation (ICRA), May 2021, pp. 8252–8258. doi: 10.1109/ICRA48506.2021.9562070.\n",
    "\n",
    "> [3] A. Hashimoto and N. Abaid, ‘An Agent-Based Model of Lost Person Dynamics for Enabling Wilderness Search and Rescue’, presented at the ASME 2019 Dynamic Systems and Control Conference, Nov. 2019. doi: 10.1115/DSCC2019-9222."
   ]

    "from Behaviour import BehaviourVector, BehaviourEnum"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Create all vector permutations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "step = 0.2\n",
    "it = np.arange(0,1+step,step)\n",
    "vecs = np.meshgrid(*(it,)*6)\n",
    "vecs = np.vstack([f.flatten() for f in vecs])\n",
    "vecs = vecs[:, np.sum(vecs,axis=0)==1]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 2400x2400 with 1 Axes>",

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,8),dpi=300)\n",
    "\n",
    "x = np.arange(0,vecs.shape[1])\n",
    "\n",
    "bottom = np.zeros(vecs.shape[1])\n",
    "for i, behaviour in enumerate(BehaviourEnum):\n",
    "    ax.bar(x,vecs[i,:],bottom=bottom, width=1)\n",
    "    bottom += vecs[i,:]"
   ]

    "## Import GeoTIFF image with slope data\n",
    "\n",
    "> [4]: Lidar Composite Digital Terrain Model Scotland (Phase2) 1m resolution [ASC geospatial data], Scale 1:4000, Tiles: nr82ne,nr83se,nr92nw,nr92sw,nr93sw,nr91ne,nr92ne,nr92se,nr93se,ns02ne,ns02nw,ns02se,ns02sw,ns03se,ns03sw, Updated: 1 July 2014, Non-Commercial Government Licence, Using: EDINA LIDAR Digimap Service, <https://digimap.edina.ac.uk>, Downloaded: 2022-01-28 13:08:03.643"

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Canny edge detection\n",
    "https://scikit-image.org/docs/dev/auto_examples/edges/plot_canny.html"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from skimage import feature\n",
    "\n",
    "slope_data = slope.read(1)\n",
    "slope_data[slope_data<0] = 0\n",
    "edges_rough = feature.canny(slope_data).astype(int)\n",
    "edges = feature.canny(slope_data, sigma=3).astype(int)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "Display results"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "fig, (ax1,ax2,ax3) = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=3, figsize=(8, 3))\n",
    "\n",
    "rioplot.show(slope, cmap='gray', ax=ax1)\n",
    "ax1.set_title('Slope image')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax2.imshow(edges_rough, cmap='gray', extent=extent)\n",
    "ax2.set_title(r'Canny filter, $\\sigma=1$')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax3.imshow(edges, cmap='gray', extent=extent)\n",
    "ax3.set_title(r'Canny filter, $\\sigma=3$')\n",
    "\n",
    "for a in [ax1,ax2,ax3]:\n",
    "    a.axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

     "data": {

      "image/png": "\n"
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, (ax1,ax2,ax3) = plt.subplots(1,3,figsize=(12,12), dpi=300, subplot_kw={'aspect':1})\n",
    "\n",
    "rioplot.show(sim.env.edges, cmap='gray', ax=ax1)\n",
    "rioplot.show(sim.env.slope, cmap='gray', ax=ax3)\n",
    "\n",
    "max_x, min_x = -np.inf, np.inf\n",
    "max_y, min_y = -np.inf, np.inf\n",
    "\n",
    "x_path = {k: [f.x for f in v['coords']] for k,v in sim.long_term_ds.items()}\n",
    "y_path = {k: [f.y for f in v['coords']] for k,v in sim.long_term_ds.items()}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in x_path.keys():\n",
    "    x, y = np.array([x_path[i], y_path[i]])\n",
    "    x, y = list(riotrans.xy(sim.env.edges.profile['transform'], x, y))\n",
    "\n",
    "    max_x = max(max_x, np.max(x))\n",
    "    min_x = min(min_x, np.min(x))\n",
    "    max_y = max(max_y, np.max(y))\n",
    "    min_y = min(min_y, np.min(y))\n",
    "    [ax.plot(x, y) for ax in [ax2,ax3]]\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax in [ax1,ax2,ax3]:\n",
    "    ax.set_ylim([min_y-50, 50+max_y])\n",
    "    ax.set_xlim([min_x-50, 50+max_x])\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel(\"y (m)\")\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel(\"x (m)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax1.set_title(\"Edges\")\n",
    "ax2.set_title(\"All paths\")\n",
    "ax3.set_title(\"Paths over slope\")\n",
    "fig.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "Validate the Line Following visually"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 864x864 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": "\n"
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "lf_results = next(filter( lambda x: x['bvec'] == BehaviourVector(rw=0,lf=1,st=0,sp=0,bt=0,ve=0).tolist(), sim.long_term_ds.values()), None)\n",
    "\n",
    "def plot(res: dict[str,list[Coord]], dataset: rasterio.DatasetReader = None):\n",
    "    if dataset is None:\n",
    "        dataset = sim.env.edges\n",
    "\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,12), subplot_kw={'aspect':1})\n",
    "    x, y = np.array([[f.x for f in res['coords']], [f.y for f in res['coords']]])\n",
    "    x,y = riotrans.xy(dataset.profile['transform'], x, y)\n",
    "\n",
    "    min_x, max_x = np.min(x), np.max(x)\n",
    "    min_y, max_y = np.min(y), np.max(y)\n",
    "\n",
    "    rioplot.show(dataset, cmap='gray', ax=ax)\n",
    "    ax.set_ylim([min_y-5, max_y+5])\n",
    "    ax.set_xlim([min_x-5, max_x+5])\n",
    "    ax.plot(x,y)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "plot(lf_results)"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Use agent to generate PDM\n",
    "TODO: Select \"best\" agent. Pick one at random for now\n",
    "\n",
    "> Simulations were run for the time it would take for a\n",
    "person to walk an hour with an average pace of 4 kilometers an\n",
    "hour and with a time step of 6 seconds, that is T = 600.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [3]\n",
    "\n",
    "Thus, each cell is $5m$ wide. Not accounting for diagonal steps, slope, etc., we run the simulation for $800$ timesteps."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "  0%|          | 0/20000 [00:00<?, ?it/s]",
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0,
       "model_id": "aef9d584e870416bb554bc203683a9f3"
      }
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "agent = BehaviourVector(rw=0.05,lf=0.5,st=0.1,sp=0.0, bt=0.05, ve=0.3 ) # it's probably the most interesting\n",
    "\n",
    "n_trials = 20000\n",
    "n_steps = 150\n",
    "start = Coord(x=1900,y=2000)\n",
    "\n",
    "def bvecs():\n",
    "    for _ in tqdm(range(n_trials)):\n",
    "        yield copy.deepcopy(agent)\n",
    "\n",
    "old_cd = SixDSim.collect_data\n",
    "def monkeypatch_collect_data(self, ps: Coord) -> None:\n",
    "    self.data_store = (ps.x, ps.y)\n",
    "SixDSim.collect_data = monkeypatch_collect_data\n",
    "\n",
    "pdm_sim = SixDSim(start, bvecs=bvecs())\n",
    "pdm_sim.trials(n_steps)\n",
    "SixDSim.collect_data = old_cd"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 54,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "end_locations = np.array([f for f in pdm_sim.long_term_ds.values()])\n",
    "\n",
    "x,y = riotrans.xy(pdm_sim.env.edges.profile['transform'], end_locations[:,0], end_locations[:,1])\n",
    "\n",
    "min_x = np.min(x)\n",
    "max_x = np.max(x)\n",
    "min_y = np.min(y)\n",
    "max_y = np.max(y)\n",
    "z = np.zeros((int(max_y-min_y+1), int(max_x-min_x+1)))\n",
    "\n",
    "for xi, yi in zip(x,y):\n",
    "    x_ = int(xi - min_x)\n",
    "    y_ = int(yi -min_y)\n",
    "\n",
    "    z[y_,x_] += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "z = ski.filters.gaussian(z, 2)\n",
    "z = np.ma.masked_where(z == 0, z)\n",
    "z /= np.sum(z)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 57,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 2400x2400 with 2 Axes>",
      "image/png": "\n"
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,8),dpi=300)\n",
    "\n",
    "rioplot.show(pdm_sim.env.slope, cmap='gray', ax=ax)\n",
    "\n",
    "extent = [min_x, max_x, min_y, max_y]\n",
    "\n",
    "z_plt = ax.imshow(z, cmap='jet', interpolation='None', extent=extent, alpha=0.6)\n",
    "fig.colorbar(z_plt)\n",
    "\n",
    "start_x, start_y =  riotrans.xy(pdm_sim.env.edges.profile['transform'], (start.x), (start.y))\n",
    "ax.scatter(start_x, start_y, label='Start')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_title(f\"PDM for 4D Behaviour Vector\\n{n_trials} trials | {n_steps} steps per trial\\n{agent}\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(f\"x (m)\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(f\"y (m)\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlim([min_x, max_x])\n",
    "ax.set_ylim([min_y, max_y])\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
